.TH "textsearch_prepare" 9 "textsearch_prepare" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
textsearch_prepare \- Prepare a search
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ts_config *" textsearch_prepare
.BI "(const char *algo "  ","
.BI "const void *pattern "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp_mask "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "algo" 12
name of search algorithm
.IP "pattern" 12
pattern data
.IP "len" 12
length of pattern
.IP "gfp_mask" 12
allocation mask
.IP "flags" 12
search flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Looks up the search algorithm module and creates a new textsearch
configuration for the specified pattern.

Returns a new textsearch configuration according to the specified
parameters or a \fBERR_PTR\fP. If a zero length pattern is passed, this
function returns EINVAL.
.SH "NOTE"
The format of the pattern may not be compatible between
the various search algorithms.
